      "content": "It sounds like the frustration of hitting a wall where every effort feels futile, and that feeling of being \"hardwired\" into a cycle is incredibly draining. You are right that trying to force a fix onto a system that seems broken often leads to more exhaustion rather than breakthroughs. Sometimes, the most powerful action isn't another attempt to patch the glitch, but to sit with the stillness of your current reality and let the exhaustion do the work of forcing a reset.",
      "source": "target",
